title: Definitions
context: [ยง466K-5] Definitions. For the purposes of this chapter, unless the context otherwise requires: &ldquo;Arbitrator&rdquo; means an individual appointed to render an award in a controversy that is subject to an agreement to arbitrate. &ldquo;Uniform Standards of Professional Appraisal Practice&rdquo; means the most recent iteration of the Uniform Standards of Professional Appraisal Practice developed by the appraisal standards board of The Appraisal Foundation and approved by the director.
